# radon-lite project memory

## Project Overview
TypeScript/Node HTTP server wrapping the `simulator-server` binary (Rust, arm64 macOS) to control iOS simulators via a clean REST API for humans + AI agents. Git repo on `main` branch. Initial commit done.

## Key Files
- `simulator-server` — binary in project root, Mach-O arm64, version 1.20.0
- `src/config.ts` — CLI args/env var parser, exports `config` singleton
- `src/server.ts` — Express app factory, mounts all routes + fingerprint/token endpoints
- `src/index.ts` — entry point
- `src/types/index.ts` — all shared TypeScript types
- `src/services/SimulatorServerProcess.ts` — wraps binary process, full stdin/stdout protocol, EventEmitter
- `src/services/SessionManager.ts` — session lifecycle (create/get/list/destroy/toPublic)
- `src/services/SimulatorService.ts` — xcrun simctl + binary helper commands
- `src/routes/simulators.ts` — simulator list/boot/shutdown routes
- `src/routes/sessions.ts` — all session endpoints including SSE

## Token System
- Binary requires an ES256 JWT containing `cp_fpr` (machine fingerprint) — NOT a license key
- Get fingerprint: `GET /fingerprint` or `./simulator-server fingerprint`
- This machine's fingerprint: `5220ebeee9fbccff39a1530945e9e2b73f043918c784bff351747e02e43ce24c`
- Verify JWT: `POST /token/verify { token }` or `./simulator-server verify_token <JWT>`
- Activate license key → JWT: `POST /token/activate { licenseKey, name? }` — calls `https://portal.ide.swmansion.com/api/create-token`
- Portal activation error codes: `E000`=success, `E001`=notFound, `E002`=noSubscription
- The base64-encoded JSON `{"a":...,"t":...,"s":...}` is the Radon IDE **license activation key**, NOT the JWT
- Features like Screenshot, ScreenRecording, ScreenReplay require Pro/Team/Enterprise JWT
- Free tier: touch/key/button/rotate/paste/scroll + MJPEG stream work without token

## simulator-server Binary Protocol
**Launch:** `./simulator-server ios --id <UDID> [-t <JWT_TOKEN>]`

**Stdout messages (parse line by line):**
- `stream_ready http://127.0.0.1:<port>/stream.mjpeg`
- `fps_report {"fps":N,"received":N,"dropped":N,"timestamp":N}`
- `video_ready <id> <url> <filepath>` — id is "recording" or "replay"
- `video_error <id> <message>`
- `screenshot_ready <id> <url> <filepath>`
- `screenshot_error <id> <message>`
- `token_valid <plan>` / `token_invalid <reason>` (reasons: corrupted/expired/fingerprint_mismatch/unknown)

**Stdin commands:**
- `pointer show true/false`
- `video replay start -m -b 50` / `video replay stop`
- `video replay save -r <orientation> -d 5 -d 10 -d 30` → emits one `video_ready replay` per duration
- `video recording start -b 2000` / `video recording stop` / `video recording save -r <orientation>`
- `screenshot <id> [-r <orientation>]`
- `touch Down/Up/Move <x,y> [<x2,y2>]` — coords normalized 0.0–1.0
- `key Down/Up <keycode>`
- `button Down/Up home/back/power/volumeUp/volumeDown/appSwitch/actionButton`
- `rotate Portrait/LandscapeLeft/LandscapeRight/PortraitUpsideDown`
- `paste START-SIMSERVER-PASTE>>><text><<<END-SIMSERVER-PASTE`
- `wheel <x,y> --dx <dx> --dy <dy>`
- `token <JWT>` — update token at runtime
- `fps true/false`

**Known behavior:**
- Paywalled commands (screenshot, recording, replay) with no/invalid token: binary silently ignores them — server has 15s timeout (`MEDIA_TIMEOUT_MS`) to avoid hanging
- Replay returns "full" duration if buffer doesn't have enough footage for the requested duration
- Binary serves media (screenshots, videos) at `http://127.0.0.1:<port>/media/<filename>`
- Binary stderr: set `SIMSERVER_LOG` env var to control log level

## API Summary
```
GET  /config
GET  /fingerprint
POST /token/verify           { token }
POST /token/activate         { licenseKey, name? }

GET  /simulators
GET  /simulators/running
POST /simulators/:udid/boot
POST /simulators/:udid/shutdown

POST   /sessions             { udid, token?, replay?, showTouches? }
GET    /sessions
GET    /sessions/:id
DELETE /sessions/:id
PUT    /sessions/:id/token   { token }
PUT    /sessions/:id/settings { replay?, showTouches? }

GET  /sessions/:id/stream
POST /sessions/:id/screenshot  { rotation? }
POST /sessions/:id/record/start
POST /sessions/:id/record/stop { rotation? }
POST /sessions/:id/replay      { rotation?, durations? }  — default durations [5,10,30]
POST /sessions/:id/input/touch   { type: "Down"|"Up"|"Move", points: [{x,y}] }
POST /sessions/:id/input/key     { direction: "Down"|"Up", keyCode: number }
POST /sessions/:id/input/button  { direction: "Down"|"Up", button: "home"|"back"|"power"|"volumeUp"|"volumeDown"|"appSwitch"|"actionButton" }
POST /sessions/:id/input/rotate  { orientation: "Portrait"|"LandscapeLeft"|"LandscapeRight"|"PortraitUpsideDown" }
POST /sessions/:id/input/paste   { text: string }
POST /sessions/:id/input/scroll  { x, y, deltaX, deltaY }
GET  /sessions/:id/events        (SSE: screenshot_ready, screenshot_error, video_ready, video_error, fps_report, exit)
```

## SSE Event Format
```
event: screenshot_ready
data: {"id":"...","url":"http://...","filePath":"..."}

event: video_ready
data: {"id":"recording"|"replay","durationSecs":5|"full","url":"...","filePath":"..."}

event: fps_report
data: {"fps":60,"received":100,"dropped":0,"timestamp":1234567890}
```

## Startup Args
`node dist/index.js [--port N] [--replay|--no-replay] [--show-touches|--no-show-touches]`
Defaults: port=3000, replay=true, showTouches=true
Env vars: PORT, REPLAY, SHOW_TOUCHES

## Build & Run
```bash
npm run build   # tsc → dist/
npm start       # node dist/index.js
npm run dev     # ts-node (no build needed)
```

## Testing Quick Reference
1. `npm start`
2. `curl http://localhost:3000/simulators/running` — find a booted UDID
3. `curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/sessions -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"udid":"<UDID>","token":"<JWT>"}'`
4. Open `streamUrl` in browser for live MJPEG feed
5. `curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/sessions/<id>/screenshot` → PNG URL
6. `curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/sessions/<id>/replay -d '{"durations":[5]}'` → .mp4 URL

## packages/tool-server — Tool List (10 tools)
- `list-simulators`, `boot-simulator`, `simulator-server` (original 3)
- `screenshot` (outputHint: "image" — requires Pro JWT)
- `tap`, `swipe`, `gesture`, `button`, `paste`, `rotate` (interaction tools via WebSocket)
- All interaction tools call `ensureServer(udid)` — auto-spawns binary if needed
- `simulator-registry.ts` — shared module: process Map + WS Map + `ensureServer` + `sendCommand` + `httpScreenshot`
- `simulator-server.ts` registers spawn fn via `registerSpawnFn(spawnAndWait)` at module load
- `ws` package for WebSocket; command format: `{ id: "1", cmd: "touch"|"button"|"paste"|"rotate", ...fields }`

## packages/mcp
- ESM-only (`"type": "module"`), NodeNext tsconfig, separate from root tsconfig
- Entry: `packages/mcp/dist/index.js` — thin MCP bridge ~90 lines
- Discovers tools dynamically from `GET /tools` — no hardcoding
- `outputHint: "image"` → fetches PNG URL, returns base64 image to MCP client
- Config: `.claude/mcp.json` — `RADON_TOOLS_URL=http://localhost:3001`

## packages/skills
- 4 skill files in `packages/skills/skills/`: simulator-setup.md, simulator-screenshot.md, simulator-interact.md, test-ui-flow.md
- Install: `node packages/skills/scripts/install.js` → copies to `.claude/skills/`

## packages/ui (React Webview)
- React 19 + Vite + Tailwind — `cd packages/ui && npm run dev`
- Open at `http://localhost:5173?serverUrl=http://localhost:3000`
- **Adapters:** `VsCodeAdapter` (acquireVsCodeApi) and `StandaloneAdapter` (query param / localStorage)
- **State machine** in `App.tsx`: waiting-for-url → picking-device → session-active → token-needed
- **Token flow:** UI never calls activation API; sends `requestToken` to host, host replies `setToken`
- `MjpegCanvas`: hidden `<img>` + rAF `<canvas>` draw + 2s decode watchdog for reconnect
- `TouchSurface`: pointer events → normalized [0,1] coords → `api.touch` / `api.scroll`
- Theme: CSS custom properties (`--rl-*`) with VSCode override via `body[data-platform="vscode"]`
- Build: `npm run build` → `dist/` (tsc + vite build, ~210 kB JS gzipped ~66 kB)

## Known Issues / Future Work
- Sessions stay in map after process dies (state shows "dead" but entry not auto-cleaned)
- No persistence — sessions lost on server restart
- No OpenAPI/Swagger docs yet (useful for AI agent tool discovery)
- `POST /token/activate` portal call may return E002 if key already claimed by a different fingerprint
- Consider adding `GET /sessions/:id/screenshot/latest` that returns the PNG as an image response (useful for AI vision)
